Business Brief -- Hovnanian Enterprises Inc.:
   Housing Developer Reports
   Improved Results for Period
The housing developer posted net income of $218,000, or
one cent a share, for the period ended Nov. 30, compared with
a net loss of $17.5 million, or 84 cents a share, a year
earlier. The 1990 third-quarter results included a non-cash
charge of $14 million, or 67 cents a share. Revenue increased
to $80.2 million from $60.4 million.
   The Red Bank, N.J., company noted that new-home orders
more than doubled in its core Northeast region and were up
20% in its North Carolina division, while results in Florida
remained sluggish. "Our New Jersey market share is growing,"
said Kevork S. Hovnanian, chairman. "We are now positioned to
make profits even in this recessionary economy."